        <p>When you view <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp Plus" /> output on your local computer, Flare creates a special folder called "MCPreview" within your "C:\Inetpub\wwwroot" folder, and it places a copy of your <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp Plus" /> output files in it. This enables you to test the advanced features of <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.WebHelp Plus" /> on your local machine. (For <MadCap:keyword term="Microsoft Windows Vista" />Windows Vista users testing locally, the physical location is C:\MadCap\[Name of Project]\[Name of Main Entry File].htm.)</p>
